Three people died in a road
accident on Nairobi-Mombasa highway at Manyani, Voi, on Tuesday morning.  The 7 am accident occurred as the driver of a saloon car heading to Mombasa attempted to overtake another car. He collided with a trailer. Taita Taveta police commander Fred Ochieng' said the car's occupants died at the scene. "The truck driver escaped," he told The Star. Ochieng' asked drivers to obey traffic rules to preventaccidents.  Related: Mum, four-year-old girl killed in Garissa accident Read more: NTSA, KeNHA put drivers on notice after December accidents kill 150 Click
